s and figures, the authors identify long-term changes in Hungary from the late 1940s to the late 1980s and provide an in-depth analysis of the impact of the collapse of the communist system in the 1990s. They also compare long-term and shor-term change in Hungary with trends in other Central and Eastern European countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aEconomic stabilizationzHungary. 0aPost-communismzHungary. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a20th century Communism.  aCustoms and traditions.  aDemography.  aEducation, Modernization, Transition.1 aAndorka, Rudolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndorka, Rudolf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFábián, Zoltán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarcsa, István, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolosi, Tamás, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolosi, Tamás, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLengyel, György, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRóbert, Péter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSik, Endre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTóka, Gábor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTóth, István György, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVukovich, György, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVukovich, György, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package: